webpackJsonp([65380673165540],{1395:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Psyked.co.uk",author:"James Ford"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/James/Repositories/portfolio-2018/src/posts/simple-box2d-better-cleverer-more-optimised/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p><img src="http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/box2d-shapes-2.jpg" title="box2d-shapes-2"></p>\n<p><em>^ This time, that\'s an image - saves on the page rendering time!</em></p>\n<p>Another update on the Box2D classes I\'m working on.  No new features, but some pretty cool expansions and improvements to the library object creation.</p>\n<p>If you check out <a href="http://www.psyked.co.uk/box2d/demo-source-simple-box2d-with-curved-edges.htm">the previous post</a>, you\'ll see that the the dynamically drawn shapes weren\'t exactly perfect; nor were they very efficient.  Oh they worked fine, and traced the detail of the shape very well - but it took a decent chunk of system resources to animate and ended up with some overlaid shapes; which all made the Box2D a bit sluggish and the behaviours buggy.</p>\n<p>So, stealing incorporating ideas from other projects has been the name of the game - namely the ear clipping optimisation code from <a href="http://www.splashdust.net/2009/10/box2d-mouse-drawing-now-with-ear-clipping/">Splashdust.net</a>, combined with some of my own cobbled-together more optimised code for tracing curved edges.</p>\n<h3>Live demo:</h3>\n<p>Mouse interaction is enabled in the below example - click and drag the objects to check out how it works.</p>\n<p>[kml_flashembed movie="<a href="http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/LettersExperiment.swf">http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/LettersExperiment.swf</a>" height="280" width="500" /]</p>\n<h3><a href="http://uploads.psyked.co.uk/2010/02/simplebox2d_demo_100202.zip">Download the source code for this demo.</a></h3>\n<p>* The source code isn\'t exactly cleaned up - sometime, eventually, it will be.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Simple Box2D - Better, cleverer, more optimised.",date:"February 03, 2010",tags:["box2d","actionscript"]}}},pathContext:{}}}});
